  "description": "The dish uses South Indian evening-tiffin logic: quick-cooking grains, legumes, and aromatic tempering for depth without richness. Ragi Mudde with Keerai Saaru brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Bring 360 ml water with salt to a rolling boil over high heat. Rain in the flour while stirring briskly; lower to medium-low and beat for 5 to 6 minutes until thick and glossy.",
    "With wet hands, shape the hot cooked dough into 4 compact balls once cool enough to handle.",
    "For the saaru, simmer dal, vegetable, tomato, garlic, cumin, pepper, and 260 ml water for 10 minutes on medium heat until lightly broth-like.",
    "Serve the mudde hot with the saaru poured alongside or over torn pieces."
  ],
